HEADWORD: Disquiettude
<hw>Dis*qui"et*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Want of peace
or tranquility; uneasiness; disturbance; agitation; anxiety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fears and <qex>disquietude</qex>, and unavoidable anxieties of
mind.</q> <rj><qau>Abp. Sharp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disquisition</ent>⟦br⟧
